Description: FedNow Service Scope

The common response is the message a FedNow participant uses to provide the status of a return request (camt.056), an RFP cancellation request (camt.055) or an information request (camt.026) previously sent by another FedNow participant.

FedNow Service Usage

1. Return Request Response Usage

The return request response delivered by the FedNow Service to the FedNow participant that sent a return request either informs that the request has been rejected by the FedNow Service for failing the FedNow Service business validation, or contains the response of the FedNow participant that received the return request (i.e., the Creditor Agent) that the FedNow Service delivers. 

If a FedNow participant receiving the return request (camt.056) message wants to inform the sender of the request that the request is either not going to be honored or is still pending, then the FedNow participant will only send the return request response. 

If the FedNow participant intends to honor the return request, then the FedNow participant should send the return request response to inform the FedNow participant and send a payment return (pacs.004) message.

2. RFP Cancellation Request Response Usage

The request for payment cancellation request response delivered by the FedNow Service to the FedNow participant that sent a request for payment cancellation request either informs that the request has been rejected by the FedNow Service for failing the FedNow Service business validation, or contains the response of the FedNow participant that received the request for payment cancellation request (i.e., the Debtor Agent) that the FedNow Service delivers. 

If the FedNow participant that received the request for payment cancellation request (camt.055) decides to honor the request, then it should cancel the request for payment (pain.013) and send a request for payment cancellation request response to so inform the FedNow participant that sent the cancellation request. 

If the FedNow participant that received the request for payment cancellation request (camt.055) wants to inform the sender of the request that the request is either not going to be honored or is still pending, then the FedNow participant will only send the request for payment cancellation request response (camt.029).

3. Information Request Response Usage

An information request response sent by the FedNow Service to a FedNow participant contains the response from the FedNow participant that received the original information request that the FedNow Service delivers. 

If the FedNow participant receiving the information request intends to provide further information, then it should send the information request response (camt.029) to so inform the FedNow participant that sent the information request, followed by an additional payment information (camt.028) message.

If the FedNow participant receiving the information request needs to further investigate the information request, then it may send an information request response (camt.029) to so inform the FedNow participant that sent the information request.

If the FedNow participant receiving the information request cannot honor the request for information, then it should send an information request response (camt.029) to so inform the FedNow participant that sent the information request. Both FedNow participants will then need to determine their course of action. The FedNow participant that sent the initial payment instruction or request for payment message may decide to send a return request (camt.056) or a request for payment cancellation request (camt.055) respectively. The FedNow participant that sent the information request may decide to return the funds of the original payment by sending a return payment (pacs.004).
